questions.question:
Consider the languages:
L1 = {0^i 1^j | i = j}
L2 = {0^i 1^j | i = 2j}
L3 = {0^i 1^j | i+j = 2^(n+1) for some n >= 0}
L4 = {0^i 1^j | i + 2j = 2}

A. Only L3 is context free.
B. Only L2 and L3 are context free.
C. Only L1 and L2 are context free.
D. All are context free.

Consider the languages L1, L2, and L3 as given below.
L1 = {0^p 1^q | p, q in N and p = q}
L2 = {0^p 1^q 0^r | p, q, r in N and p = q}
L3 = {0^p 1^q 0^r | p, q, r in N and p = q = r}

Which of the following statements is NOT TRUE?

A. Push Down Automata (PDA) can be used to recognize L1 and L2.
B. L2 is a regular language.
C. All the three languages are context free.
D. Turing machines can be used to recognize all the languages.

Consider the following languages.
L0 = {0^p 1^q 0^r | p, q, r >= 0}
L1 = {0^p 1^q 0^r | p, q, r >= 0, p = q}
L2 = {0^p 1^q 0^r | p, q, r >= 0, 0_p != r}

Which one of the following statements is FALSE?

A. L0 is context-free.
B. L1 is context-free.
C. Complement of L2 is recursive.
D. Complement of L0 is context-free but not regular.
